      "message": "The intent of this function is to validate TestResult.status, which is not allowed to have STATUS_UNSPECIFIED.\n: \nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/resultdb/proto/v1/test_result.proto;l\u003d89-91\n\nHowever, I realized that this function can be seen as a general validator for any TestStatus enum values. All the validator functions in pbutil/test_result.go are intended to validate the corresponding field in message TestResult{}.\n\nHow about renaming this to ValidateTestResultStatus(), instead?\nIf TestResultPredicate.status is added, we can add ValidatePredicateStatus() under pbutil/predicate.go.",
